claimstats.LossCauseCd, claimstats.SubLossCauseCd, claimstats.ProductName, claimstats.PolicyProductVersionIdRef, claimstats.PolicyProductName, claimstats.PolicyTypeCd, claimstats.PolicyGroupCd, claimstats.ReversalStopInd, claimstats.CustomerRef, claimstats.AggregateLimit, claimstats.AggregateLimitDescription, claimstats.CheckDt, claimstats.CheckNumber, claimstats.CheckAmt, claimstats.CatastropheRef, claimstats.CatastropheNumber, claimstats.PropertyDamagedIdRef, claimstats.PropertyDamagedNumber, claimstats.RecordOnly, claimstats.FileReasonCd, claimstats.SystemCheckReference, claimstats.ClaimantLinkIdRef, claimstats.ServicePeriodStartDt, claimstats.ServicePeriodEndDt, claimstats.HistoricReserveAmt, claimstats.HistoricExpectedRecoveryAmt, claimstats.HistoricPaidAmt, claimstats.HistoricPostedRecoveryAmt, claimstats.ReasonCd, claimstats.DenyTypeCd, claimstats.DenyReasonCd, claimstats.NotToRepairInd, claimstats.ClaimantMaritalStatusCd, claimstats.ClaimantNumberOfDependents, claimstats.ClaimantNatureCd, claimstats.ClaimantBodyPartGeneralCd, claimstats.ClaimantBodyPartSpecificCd, claimstats.ClaimantBodyPartIAIABCCd, claimstats.ClaimantInitialTreatment, claimstats.ClaimantDisabilityTypeCd, claimstats.ClaimantClassCd, claimstats.ClaimantEmploymentStatusCd, claimstats.ClaimantShiftCd, claimstats.ClaimantHourlySalaryCd, claimstats.ClaimantAverageWeeklyWagesAmt, claimstats.ClaimantHireDt, claimstats.ClaimantLastWorkedDt, claimstats.ShortDesc, claimstats.City, claimstats.State, claimstats.FPLiabilityPer, claimstats.InsuredName, claimstats.ZipCd, claimstats.CoverageDesc, claimstats.PayToVendor, claimstats.ConversionGrp, claimstats.CoverageTriggerCd, claimstats.AwarenessDt, claimstats.MajorPerilCd, claimstats.VariableCd1, claimstats.VariableCd2, claimstats.SubLineCd, claimstats.ClaimantIdRef, claimstats.SuitStatus, claimstats.TaxId, claimstats.NumericTransactionCd, claimstats.NumericSummaryTransactionCd, claimstats.StatLineCd, claimstats.ISOCode, claimstats.ClassificationCd, claimstats.ConstructionCd, claimstats.YearBuilt, claimstats.TerritoryCd, claimstats.SprinklerCd, claimstats.ProtectionClass, claimstats.ClassCd, claimstats.CompanyNumber, claimstats.CompProgExInd, claimstats.UnderlyingPersonalLiability, claimstats.UmbEndorsementInd, claimstats.UmbPersLiabInd, claimstats.UmbAutoPolicyInd, claimstats.UmbRiskProfileInd, claimstats.NoPaymentReason, claimstats.OtherNoPaymentReason, claimstats.UpdateTimestamp 
FROM
 claimstats 
 where bookdt >= '$$m_StrtDt' and bookdt < '$$m_EndDt'
 ##also get updated records
 or (updatetimestamp >= '$$m_StrtDt' and updatetimestamp < '$$m_EndDt' and updatetimestamp > bookdt)
 or (checkdt >= updatetimestamp)

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: Exp_format_dates

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))
